Module mesakit.graph.core
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph.specifications.library.attributes

Class AttributeLoader

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.specifications.library.attributes.AttributeLoader
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.loading.Unloadable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
public class AttributeLoader extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.loading.Unloadable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
Loads attributes from a FieldArchive (note that GraphArchive is a field archive) and populates the fields of an AttributeStore through AttributeReference objects. Operations on the attribute loader for a store apply to all references. If you want to operate on just one attribute, see AttributeReference.

Attributes

  • add(AttributeReference) - Adds the given attribute reference to this loader
  • attributes() - Retrieves the attributes managed by this loader
  • supports(Attribute) - True if the given attribute is supported by this loader

Loading and Unloading

  • attach(FieldArchive) - Attaches the given field archive to load from
  • load(Attribute) - Loads the given attribute
  • loadAll() - Loads all attributes
  • loadAllExcept(AttributeSet) - Loads all attributes except for the given ones
  • loadRequired(Attribute) - Loads the given attribute, but throws an exception if this fails
  • isLoaded() - True if any attribute is loaded, false if all attributes are unloaded
  • unload() - Unloads all attributes
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
